The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 12 October is 4,025 (465.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 08 October, there were 332 new confirmed cases (38.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 01 October, there were 243 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 37% ( 89 extra cases).
